commit.message:
Add a protocol for XSD attribute groups

  - Bump minor release and update release info

Extend protocols for attributes

  - Added LxmlAttribProtocol for attributes of lxml elements
  - Fix compatibility with None keys (as in xmlschema) using
    a Union for attrib of ElementProtocol
Put all imports at the top of the files (PEP8 compliance)

Update failing __repr__ tests after changes

  - Change again __repr__ of maps and arrays: focus on evaluation

Refine type annotations

  - Sharpen type annotation of parser argument of XPath tokens
  - Add type annotations of some class variables of XPath parsers

Add a method for wrapping an XPathFunction to a standard function

  - Refactor __repr__ for tokens: readable format is useless for
    building new tokens (except for maps and arrays) so better to
    use a nearly-standard repr with id() of the token instance;
  - Split __repr__ and __str__ for parsers, using a standard repr.

Differentiate __repr__ and __str__ for XPath parsers

  - Parser __repr__() avoids excessive long representations
  - Parser __str__() gives a full string representation
  - Add arg names to token representation
  - String representation of tokens is still related to token
    readable description and full representation for maps/arrays

Simplify protocols: remove XsdAnyElementProtocol

  - ref property: only for attributes and elements ad Optional[Any]
    for not breaking nested protocols (maybe because it's None for
    wildcards)
Bump bugfix release

Remove GenericElement (keep protocols hierarchy)

  - Cannot use generics without break the hierarchy of element
    protocols: better to preserve the tree of element protocols
    using less precise annotations;
  - Add EtreeElementProtocol for xml.etree.ElementTree.Element.
Revise protocols to be compliant with XSD components

Add testenv for Python 3.13 in tox.ini

  - Fix a typo and remove deprecated decorator

Improve schema context evaluation for XPath 3.0/3.1

  - Applied to several operators and functions, but maybe many of
    them are not useful/applicable for XSD 1.1 assertions.
Improve schema context evaluation in common context-based methods
Improve schema context evaluation for XPath 1.0/2.0 tokens

Refactor schema context evaluation

  - Suppress all errors during schema context evaluation: the goal
    is to tag with XSD types all the possible tokens that can match
    an element or an attribute;
  - The static context evaluation is always done, before the schema
    context evaluation;
  - TODO: refactor of all exception handling in evaluation/select.
Exclude tests/.mypy_cache/ from source distribution

Fix fn:unparsed-text* functions and update release info

  - Use codecs.getreader() for checking resource data stream
Fix function-lookup() to set a copy of the context
Add fragment option to tree builders
Fix fn:base-uri and fn:document-uri
Extend UntypedAtomic with __round__
Bump bugfix release
Add regression test of xmlschema against W3C XSD suite
Update Sphinx configuration for RTD
Fix CI tests with Python 3.10.11
Update release info

Add function objects constructor

  - XPath1Parser.get_function() returns a function object usable
    for processing data with XPath rules;
  - TODO: this is a new feature that needs further development.
